public TestClass() { }
public TestClass(int i) { }
public static void main(String[] args) { TestClass t= new TestClass(); TestClass t1= new TestClass(10); } }
- select new TestClass(10) - introduce factory - you get the exception below
- the problem is that edits generated by one rewiter can't be easily combined. The code should be written in the following way:
- create rewriter - do all modification to the rewriter without rewriting the node - do the rewriting at the end of the try block for all modifications. - to group modifications so that the preview will look nice a group descriptions can to be passed to the ASTRewrite methods (e.g mark*(ASTNode, GroupDescription). - add all used group descriptions at the end to the change object .
